    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ranged Tactics Toolbox pg. 33</em>, <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 21</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 1 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 1 lb.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d6 (small), 1d8 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x3; <strong>Range</strong> 50 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> P; <strong>Special</strong> -</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Ranged; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Thrown</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>The kestros is an oddly shaped Bronze Age sling used for launching kestros darts. Your Strength modifier applies on damage rolls when you use a kestros, just as it does for thrown weapons. You can fire-but not load-a kestros with one hand. Loading a kestros is a move action that requires two hands and provokes attacks of opportunity. Halflings treat the kestros as a martial weapon.</p>",
